Author: Nicolas De la Cruz
Credit: Jeremy Scheaffer

Program description:
The program is to use NCurses to create a single window to display the game.
In this program the user puts input to do the following:
-m:bring up monster list
 *UP_ARROW: scroll up the monster list
 *DOWN_ARROW: scroll down the monster list 
-q:quit game
-1/b: move down-left
-2/j: move dow
-3/n: move down-right
-4/h: move left
-5/' ': do not move, skip turn
-6/l: move right
-7/y: move up-left
-8/k: move up
-9/u: move up-right
-'>': go down stairs, only if standing on '>'
-'<' go up stairs, only if standing on '<'
